There are various ways to contribute to Gentoo, even without (much) technical knowledge.

== Community ==
* Help other users by trying to answer questions on the [https://forums.gentoo.org/ Forums].
* Join in our [http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/irc.xml IRC channels].
* Subscribe in our [http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/lists.xml mailing lists].
* Start a new article or improve existing documentation in our [https://wiki.gentoo.org Wiki].

== Bugs ==
* Report bugs at our [http://bugs.gentoo.org bugzilla].
* Try to confirm open bugs by reproducing them, this helps consolidate the cause.
* Try to offer solutions for open bugs, patches and ebuilds are welcome.
* Participate in our monthly [http://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Bugday Bugday], squashing bugs together with Gentoo Developers.

== Package maintenance ==
* Report new packages and version bumps at our [http://bugs.gentoo.org bugzilla], you can also submit new [http://devmanual.gentoo.org/ ebuilds] there.
* Join the [http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/sunrise/ sunrise-project], an excellent way to contribute to the Portage tree.
* Become an arch tester; for instance, check out the arch teams [http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/base/x86/at.xml x86] and [http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/base/amd64/at/ amd64].
* [http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/qa/proxy-maintainers/index.xml Proxy-maintain] an abandoned package
* Become a [http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/devrel/handbook/handbook.xml Gentoo Developer]

